A golden jubilee is worth celebrating and it is well done by the husband of the celebrator. Recently, Kwara State literarily moved to Lagos as one of its prominent indigenes, Hon. Raheem Tunji Olawuyi, popularly known as Ajilooopin, representing Ekiti/Irepodun/ Isin/Oke-Ero federal constituency, in Kwara State, organised a grand reception to mark the 50th birthday anniversary of his wife, Chief Kudirat Ajibike Olawuyi Ajiloopin. The occasion was blessed with the royal presence of Olofa of Offa, Oba Mufutau Gbadamosi, Elegushi of Ikate Kingdom, Oba Saheed Ademola Elegushi and Olori Sekinat Aramide Elegushi, Oba Ajibola Adeola Julius, the Olusin of Ijara Isin and other traditional rulers from Kwara and Lagos states. Family members were led to the occasion by Alhaji. Azeez Olawuyi, Alhaja Nimota Alebiosu-Olawuyi, Lawyer Rasaq Olawuyi, and wives. King Wasiu Ayinde Marshal was on the bandstand as dignitaries at the event were thrilled with good music including Chief Jide Oyinloye, Hon. Adebayo Otunola of Twins Faja Nig. Ltd and Aare Abdullateef Ajeigbe and Prince Quam. While Rt. Hon. Gbajabiamila congratulated the celebrant for attaining the golden age, he extolled the virtues of Hon. Olawuyi is a performing federal legislature and a doting family man.